Hannah Overton was convicted of capital murder in the 2006 salt poisoning death of her adopted son Andrew Burd . 
  Last year her conviction was overturned because of ineffective counsel . 
  Prosecutors were set to try her again for the murder of her son but have now dropped all charges . 
  Andrew died from salt poisoning after she fed him cajun seasoning . 
  Overton has spent seven years in prison and was released before Christmas . 
  She will not face new murder charges . 
 